com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum

Class StringnumWithData<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum.Stringnum
      • com.blockwithme.util.proto.stringnum.StringnumWithData<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<String>, Collection<String>, List<String>, Set<String>

    public class StringnumWithData<E>
extends Stringnum
    StringnumWithData is a Stringnum that associate each interned Strings with with some user-defined object. We do not actually check the type of the data objects, so it could be anything or null. This object is NOT thread-safe.
    Author:
    monster
